Treasury 30-year bonds pared losses
after Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said the central
bank retains the capacity to purchase U.S. government debt after
it refrained from including the securities in a plan to buy
assets.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
